.TH arctgz 7 "2026-07-19" "arctgz 0.8.0" "Miscellaneous Information Manual"
.SH NAME
arctgz \- safety-first project lifecycle library for the arctgz archive format
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
\fBuse arctgz::{\fP
\fB    init, load_config, save_config,\fP
\fB    compile, extract, verify, diff, patch,\fP
\fB    load_recipe, extract_recipe, execute_recipe,\fP
\fB    ArctgzConfig, ArctgzManifest, FileEntry,\fP
\fB    ArctgzRecipe, RecipeStep, Compression, Encryption,\fP
\fB    ArctgzDelta, DeltaOp, ArctgzError\fP
\fB};\fP
\fBuse std::path::Path;\fP

\fBfn init(project_path: &Path, force: bool) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn load_config(project_path: &Path) -> Result<ArctgzConfig, ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn save_config(project_path: &Path, config: &ArctgzConfig) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn compile(\fP
\fB    project_path: &Path,\fP
\fB    output_path: Option<&Path>,\fP
\fB    force: bool,\fP
\fB    private_key: Option<&[u8]>,\fP
\fB    password: Option<&str>\fP
\fB) -> Result<PathBuf, ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn extract(\fP
\fB    archive_path: &Path,\fP
\fB    output_dir: &Path,\fP
\fB    force: bool,\fP
\fB    public_key: Option<&[u8]>,\fP
\fB    password: Option<&str>\fP
\fB) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn verify(\fP
\fB    archive_path: &Path,\fP
\fB    public_key: Option<&[u8]>,\fP
\fB    password: Option<&str>\fP
\fB) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn diff(base: &Path, target: &Path) -> Result<ArctgzDelta, ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn patch(\fP
\fB    base: &Path, target: &Path, delta: &ArctgzDelta,\fP
\fB    output_path: &Path, private_key: Option<&[u8]>\fP
\fB) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn load_recipe(project_path: &Path) -> Result<Option<ArctgzRecipe>, ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn extract_recipe(archive_path: &Path) -> Result<ArctgzRecipe, ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn execute_recipe(\fP
\fB    output_dir: &Path,\fP
\fB    recipe: &ArctgzRecipe,\fP
\fB    force: bool\fP
\fB) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;\fP

\fBstruct ArctgzConfig {\fP
    \fBpub name:        String,\fP
    \fBpub version:     String,\fP
    \fBpub include:     Vec<String>,\fP
    \fBpub compression: Compression,\fP
    \fBpub encryption:  Encryption,\fP
\fB}\fP

\fBstruct ArctgzManifest {\fP
    \fBpub name:        String,\fP
    \fBpub version:     String,\fP
    \fBpub created:     DateTime<Utc>,\fP
    \fBpub compression: Compression,\fP
    \fBpub files:       BTreeMap<String, FileEntry>,\fP
    \fBpub signature:   Option<String>,\fP
\fB}\fP

\fBstruct FileEntry {\fP
    \fBpub size:   u64,\fP
    \fBpub sha512: String,\fP
    \fBpub is_dir: bool,\fP
\fB}\fP

\fBstruct ArctgzRecipe {\fP
    \fBpub name:    String,\fP
    \fBpub version: String,\fP
    \fBpub steps:   Vec<RecipeStep>,\fP
\fB}\fP

\fBenum RecipeStep {\fP
    \fBCopy   { from: String, to: String },\fP
    \fBMkDir  { path: String },\fP
    \fBChmod  { path: String, mode: String },\fP
    \fBRemove { path: String },\fP
\fB}\fP

\fBenum Compression {\fP
    \fBGzip,\fP
    \fBZstd,\fP
\fB}\fP

\fBenum Encryption {\fP
    \fBNone,\fP
    \fBAes256Gcm,\fP
\fB}\fP

\fBstruct ArctgzDelta {\fP
    \fBpub base_name:            String,\fP
    \fBpub base_version:         String,\fP
    \fBpub target_name:          String,\fP
    \fBpub target_version:       String,\fP
    \fBpub base_manifest_hash:   String,\fP
    \fBpub target_manifest_hash: String,\fP
    \fBpub operations:           Vec<DeltaOp>,\fP
\fB}\fP

\fBenum DeltaOp {\fP
    \fBAdd     { path, size, sha512, is_dir },\fP
    \fBModify  { path, size, sha512, is_dir },\fP
    \fBDelete  { path },\fP
\fB}\fP

\fBenum ArctgzError { ... }\fP
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The arctgz library provides a safe, cross-platform API for the full lifecycle of an arctgz project: scaffolding, configuration, compilation into a compressed and integrity-verified archive, verified extraction, standalone verification, post-extraction recipe execution, binary delta patching, and optional AES-256-GCM encryption.
.PP
All operations enforce strict path confinement, validate metadata before touching the filesystem, and use atomic file operations to prevent corruption and TOCTOU (time-of-check to time-of-use) races.
.PP
The core functionality includes:
.IP \(bu 2
\fBinit\fP() \(en scaffold a new project directory with a default configuration and an empty resource folder.
.IP \(bu
\fBload_config\fP() / \fBsave_config\fP() \(en read and write validated project configuration.
.IP \(bu
\fBcompile\fP() \(en create a compressed archive (gzip or zstd) with SHA-512 hashes and a manifest; supports parallel hashing, glob includes, empty directories, optional Ed25519 signatures, and optional AES-256-GCM encryption.
.IP \(bu
\fBextract\fP() \(en unpack an archive with full integrity checks, path traversal prevention, and automatic decryption if needed.
.IP \(bu
\fBverify\fP() \(en check archive integrity without writing files; also verifies optional signatures and decrypts if needed.
.IP \(bu
\fBdiff\fP() / \fBpatch\fP() \(en create and apply binary deltas for efficient updates between archive versions.
.IP \(bu
\fBload_recipe\fP() / \fBextract_recipe\fP() / \fBexecute_recipe\fP() \(en manage and execute post-extraction recipes (copy, mkdir, chmod, remove).
.PP
All paths are resolved with \fBstd::fs::canonicalize\fP() (equivalent to \fBrealpath\fP(3)), so symbolic links are followed during the home-directory confinement check.
The library is fully tested on Linux, macOS, and Windows.
.SH INSTALLATION
This man page can be installed system-wide using the provided installer script:
.PP
.nf
\fBcurl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mroczect/arctgz/master/install-manpage.sh | bash\fP
.fi
.PP
The script places \fBarctgz.7\fP into \fB/usr/local/share/man/man7/\fP and updates the man database.
To uninstall, run:
.PP
.nf
\fBcurl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mroczect/arctgz/master/install-manpage.sh | bash -s -- uninstall\fP
.fi
.SH FUNCTIONS
.TP
\fBinit\fP(\fIproject_path\fP, \fIforce\fP)
Initialises a new arctgz project at \fIproject_path\fP.
Creates the directory, an \fBinclude/\fP subdirectory, and a default \fBarctgz.init\fP file.
The default configuration includes \fB"compression": "gzip"\fP and \fB"encryption": "None"\fP.
See \fBArctgzConfig\fP for details.
.PP
Security checks are performed before any filesystem changes; a failed call leaves no side effects.
.TP
\fBload_config\fP(\fIproject_path\fP)
Reads and validates \fBarctgz.init\fP.
.TP
\fBsave_config\fP(\fIproject_path\fP, \fIconfig\fP)
Atomically writes a validated \fBArctgzConfig\fP back to disk (temp file + rename).
.TP
\fBcompile\fP(\fIproject_path\fP, \fIoutput_path\fP, \fIforce\fP, \fIprivate_key\fP, \fIpassword\fP)
Compiles the project into an \fB.artgz\fP archive.
.PP
\fIoutput_path\fP specifies the exact output file; if \fBNone\fP, defaults to \fBproject_path/archive.artgz\fP.
.PP
\fIforce\fP controls overwriting an existing file.
.PP
If \fIprivate_key\fP is provided (32-byte Ed25519 secret key), the manifest is signed and the signature embedded in the archive.
.PP
If the configuration's \fBencryption\fP field is set to \fBAes256Gcm\fP, \fIpassword\fP must be supplied; the final archive is encrypted with AES-256-GCM using an Argon2-derived key.
.PP
Include patterns may contain glob wildcards (e.g. \fB*.txt\fP, \fBassets/**/*.png\fP).
Empty directories that match a pattern are preserved as directory entries in the archive.
Symlinks are rejected.
.TP
\fBextract\fP(\fIarchive_path\fP, \fIoutput_dir\fP, \fIforce\fP, \fIpublic_key\fP, \fIpassword\fP)
Extracts an archive with full verification.
Compression is detected automatically; encrypted archives are decrypted on the fly if \fIpassword\fP is correct.
If \fIpublic_key\fP is provided, the manifest signature is verified before extraction.
Path traversal (absolute paths, \fB..\fP, empty, \fB.\fP) is rejected.
Existing files are overwritten only when \fBforce\fP is \fBtrue\fP.
.TP
\fBverify\fP(\fIarchive_path\fP, \fIpublic_key\fP, \fIpassword\fP)
Standalone integrity check.
Validates every file's hash and size, ensures manifest consistency, checks for unsafe paths, and optionally verifies a signature and decrypts the archive.
No files are written.
.TP
\fBdiff\fP(\fIbase_archive\fP, \fItarget_archive\fP)
Computes a binary delta between two archives.
Returns an \fBArctgzDelta\fP containing the minimal set of \fBAdd\fP, \fBModify\fP, and \fBDelete\fP operations needed to transform the base archive into the target.
Metadata files (\fBarctgz.init\fP, \fBrecipe.json\fP) are ignored during comparison.
.TP
\fBpatch\fP(\fIbase\fP, \fItarget\fP, \fIdelta\fP, \fIoutput_path\fP, \fIprivate_key\fP)
Applies a previously computed delta to the base archive, producing a new archive that is bit-for-bit identical to the original target.
The base's unchanged files are copied directly; modified or added files are taken from the target archive.
If \fIprivate_key\fP is provided, the new manifest is signed.
.TP
\fBload_recipe\fP(\fIproject_path\fP)
Loads and validates \fBrecipe.json\fP from a project directory. Returns \fBOk(None)\fP if absent.
.TP
\fBextract_recipe\fP(\fIarchive_path\fP)
Extracts and validates the embedded \fBrecipe.json\fP from an archive (gzip/zstd/encrypted transparently).
.TP
\fBexecute_recipe\fP(\fIoutput_dir\fP, \fIrecipe\fP, \fIforce\fP)
Runs the steps of a recipe inside \fIoutput_dir\fP.
Supported steps: \fBCopy\fP, \fBMkDir\fP, \fBChmod\fP (Unix only; returns \fBRecipeExecutionError\fP on other platforms), \fBRemove\fP.
All paths are validated; absolute, \fB..\fP, empty, and \fB.\fP are rejected.
When \fBforce\fP is \fBfalse\fP, existing files/directories cause an error.
.SH TYPES
.TP
\fBArctgzConfig\fP
Project configuration stored in \fBarctgz.init\fP.
.RS
.TP
\fBname\fP
Project name (alphanumeric, \fB-\fP, \fB_\fP; max 255 chars).
.TP
\fBversion\fP
Semantic version string.
.TP
\fBinclude\fP
List of relative resource paths or glob patterns (max 100 entries).
.TP
\fBcompression\fP
\fB"gzip"\fP (default) or \fB"zstd"\fP.
.TP
\fBencryption\fP
\fB"None"\fP (default) or \fB"Aes256Gcm"\fP.
.RE
.PP
The configuration file uses strict JSON validation; unknown fields are rejected.
.TP
\fBArctgzManifest\fP
Embedded in every archive as \fBmanifest.json\fP.
.RS
.TP
\fBname\fP, \fBversion\fP
Copied from config.
.TP
\fBcreated\fP
UTC timestamp of compilation.
.TP
\fBcompression\fP
Algorithm used for this archive.
.TP
\fBfiles\fP
\fBBTreeMap\fP from archive paths to \fBFileEntry\fP.
.TP
\fBsignature\fP
Optional hex-encoded Ed25519 signature over the manifest (with this field set to \fBNone\fP before signing).
.RE
.TP
\fBFileEntry\fP
Metadata for one file: \fBsize\fP (u64), \fBsha512\fP hex string, and \fBis_dir\fP (bool).
.TP
\fBArctgzRecipe\fP
Describes post-extraction actions.
.RS
.TP
\fBname\fP, \fBversion\fP
Recipe identity.
.TP
\fBsteps\fP
Ordered list of \fBRecipeStep\fP.
.RE
.TP
\fBRecipeStep\fP
Enum with \fBCopy\fP, \fBMkDir\fP, \fBChmod\fP, \fBRemove\fP.
.TP
\fBCompression\fP
Enum: \fBGzip\fP, \fBZstd\fP.
.TP
\fBEncryption\fP
Enum: \fBNone\fP, \fBAes256Gcm\fP.
.TP
\fBArctgzDelta\fP
Describes the difference between two archives.
.TP
\fBDeltaOp\fP
Enum: \fBAdd\fP, \fBModify\fP, \fBDelete\fP. Each carries path, size, SHA-512, and an \fBis_dir\fP flag (except \fBDelete\fP).
.TP
\fBArctgzError\fP
All failure variants, now including \fBSignatureError\fP, \fBKeyError\fP, \fBDeltaError\fP, and \fBEncryptionError\fP.
.SH EXAMPLE
.SS Initialising a project with zstd compression and encryption
.nf
\fBuse arctgz::{init, load_config, save_config, Compression, Encryption};\fP

\fBfn main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {\fP
    \fBlet project = Path::new("./my-project");\fP
    \fBinit(project, false)?;\fP
    \fBlet mut cfg = load_config(project)?;\fP
    \fBcfg.compression = Compression::Zstd;\fP
    \fBcfg.encryption = Encryption::Aes256Gcm;\fP
    \fBsave_config(project, &cfg)?;\fP
    \fBOk(())\fP
\fB}\fP
.fi
.SS Compile, sign, verify and extract an encrypted archive
.nf
\fBuse arctgz::{compile, verify, extract};\fP
\fBlet archive = compile(project, None, false, Some(&private_key), Some("secret"))?;\fP
\fBverify(&archive, Some(&public_key), Some("secret"))?;\fP
\fBlet out = Path::new("/tmp/out");\fP
\fBextract(&archive, out, false, Some(&public_key), Some("secret"))?;\fP
.fi
.SS Creating and applying a delta
.nf
\fBuse arctgz::{diff, patch};\fP
\fBlet delta = diff(&base_archive, &target_archive)?;\fP
\fBlet output = Path::new("./update.artgz");\fP
\fBpatch(&base_archive, &target_archive, &delta, output, None)?;\fP
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
\fBarctgz.init\fP
Project configuration (JSON). Strict validation; unknown fields rejected.
.TP
\fBinclude/\fP
Resource directory (source of archived files).
.TP
\fBrecipe.json\fP (optional)
Post-extraction recipe.
.TP
\fB<output>.artgz\fP
The compiled (and optionally encrypted) archive.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fBHOME\fP (Unix) / \fBUSERPROFILE\fP (Windows)
Home directory used for path confinement (via \fBdirs\fP crate).
.SH SECURITY
.IP \(bu 2
Home-directory confinement for \fBinit\fP.
.IP \(bu
No side effects before validation.
.IP \(bu
Atomic writes (config, archive).
.IP \(bu
Archive integrity via SHA-512 manifest (hash and size).
.IP \(bu
Ed25519 signature verification (optional).
.IP \(bu
AES-256-GCM encryption with Argon2 key derivation (optional).
.IP \(bu
Path traversal prevention in extraction, verification, and recipes.
.IP \(bu
Symlink rejection during compilation.
.IP \(bu
Strict JSON validation (deny unknown fields) for configuration and recipes.
.SH NOTES
The library does not provide internal locking; concurrent operations on the same project may lead to races.
Every individual write operation is atomic, so partial corruption is avoided.
.SH VERSION
arctgz 0.8.0 \(en adds AES-256-GCM encryption, binary delta patching, glob-based include patterns, empty directory preservation, and a revised compilation API with direct output path and password support.
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBsemver\fP(7), \fBrealpath\fP(3), \fBserde_json\fP(5), \fBdirs\fP(7), \fBflate2\fP(7), \fBzstd\fP(1), \fBtar\fP(5), \fBsha2\fP(7), \fBrayon\fP(7), \fBed25519-dalek\fP(7), \fBaes-gcm\fP(7), \fBargon2\fP(7)
.SH BUGS
.IP \(bu 2
The \fBinclude/\fP directory is always empty initially; files must be added manually.
.IP \(bu
No cryptographic signatures for encrypted archives beyond the inner Ed25519 manifest signature; encryption provides confidentiality but not non-repudiation.
.IP \(bu
\fBChmod\fP step is not supported on non-Unix platforms and returns an error.
